I recently played against a guy who used his flicker ability with [Stonehorn Dignitary](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Stonehorn Dignitary). Never having a combat phase really destroy's an deck that uses combat to deal damage.  

@Mechakraken  

The text on Venser says "Exile Target Permanent." A card is not a permanent until it is on the battlefield. Even if you own it. Even so, if Phage comes into play anyway other than you casting her, you lose, so you couldn't flicker her.
